      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">42.1501</ph> General.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2547e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2568e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                   Past performance information (including
the ratings and supporting narratives) is relevant information,
for future source selection purposes, regarding a contractor’s actions
under previously awarded contracts or orders. It includes, for example,
the contractor’s record of-</p>
               <ol id="d2547e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2568e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                         Conforming
to requirements and to standards of good workmanship;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2568e36" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                         Forecasting
and controlling costs;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2568e45" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                         Adherence
to schedules, including the administrative aspects of performance;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2568e54" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                         Reasonable
and cooperative behavior and commitment to customer satisfaction;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2568e63" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        
                         Reporting
into databases (see subpart <xref href="FAR-i1121746.dita#i1121746"
                              base="i1121746"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">4.14</xref>,
and reporting requirements in the solicitation provisions and clauses referenced
in <xref href="FAR-i1116212.dita#i1116212"
                              base="i1116212"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.104-7</xref>);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2568e79" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                        
                         Integrity
and business ethics; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2568e88" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph>
                        
                         Business-like
concern for the interest of the customer.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2568e99" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                   
                  <ph rev="FAC 2019-06 October 10, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-005?>Agencies shall monitor
their compliance with the past performance evaluation requirements
(see <xref href="FAR-i42_1502.dita#i42_1502"
                           base="i1074248"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">42.1502</xref>), and use the
Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System (CPARS) metric
tools to measure the quality and timely reporting of past performance
information. CPARS is the official source for past performance information.<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 42.1501 by revising paragraph (b).?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <msgblock props="Citation" xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre sw-d/msgblock ">[78 FR 46788, Aug. 1, 2013, as amended at 79 FR 31194, May 30, 2014]</msgblock>
